ery easy though a bit of a fiddle All in cost about 50 for the 2 doors.";i:9;s:95:"You can use a normal rubber strip on the top and bottom such as 29327 or use more brush strips.";i:10;s:107:"If your door is mounted flush with the back of the frame then you should fix the side brushes to the frame.";i:11;s:108:"You may need to loosen the screws holding the upper tracks on in order to slide the brush bracket behind it.";i:12;s:112:"Not sure if its what youre after but i had problems with damp and draughts around the bottom of our garage door.";i:13;s:118:"I screwed a batten to the bottom of the door and cut some cheap rubber car mats in half and fixed those to the batten.";i:14;s:315:"You will have to cut out to sink the footing in but the brick work will tie in with a stainless wall strip that screws on and folds out to sit between the blocks if you want to heat it you would have to line it out with celotexkingspan backed plaster board though and put a ceiling in with insulation board as well.";i:15;s:30:"Grumblegrunt LE Book Reviewer.";i:16;s:130:"Strong rubber draught seal designed to seal the gap between garage door and ground to prevent water or leaves entering the garage.";i:17;s:105:"A simple and cost-effective way of saving energy and money by reducing heat loss and preventing draughts.";i:18;s:44:"Wickes Garage Door Draught Seal Aluminium -.";i:19;s:55:"There are four main areas to consider draught-proofing.";i:20;s:74:"Keyhole buy a purpose-made cover that drops a metal disc over the keyhole.";i:21;s:94:"Letterbox use a letterbox flap or brush but remember to measure your letterbox before you buy.";i:22;s:62:"Gap at the bottom use a brush or hinged flap draught excluder.";i:23;s:141:"Watch our step-by-step video showing how to draught-proof doors with expert advice and top tips to help you complete the job with confidence.";i:24;s:14:"See the other.";i:25;s:89:"This video shows how to install a garage door weather seal to the floor beneath the door.";i:26;s:66:"This seal will prevent water snow leaves and vermin from entering.";i:27;s:39:"How do you Draught proof a garage door.";i:28;s:25:"Click to see full answer.";i:29;s:65:"Garage doors are the simplest and easiest way for mice to get in.";i:30;s:133:"If mice have chewed through the weather-stripping on the door a product like Rodent Guard can help prevent them from getting back in.";i:31;s:75:"A gap between the garage door and foundation will lead to drafts coming in.";i:32;s:100:"You can purchase an insulation kit to do this repair yourself but be sure pay attention to R-values.";i:33;s:68:"The higher the R-value the greater insulation coverage you will get.";i:34;s:71:"The most common types of insulation are foam boards or batt insulation.";i:35;s:123:"If you have an up and over garage door and you really want to keep it but stop the draughts look towards garage door seals.";i:36;s:146:"The first version of this is homemade using foam tubing which you place on the bottom lip of your garage door creating a blocker while its closed.";i:37;s:137:"Since we tend to use the garage as a front door having a clean garage floor now means that there is no dust being dragged into the house.";i:38;s:33:"It helps me keep the house clean.";i:39;s:163:"Garage Door Seal Draught Excluder Bottom Rubber Seal 48m Universal Garage Door Threshold Seal Weatherproof Weather Stripping Perfect for Keeping Garages Clean Dry.";i:40;s:65:"Polvo SUPER-SNAKE Dual Purpose Draught excluder for Garage Doors.";i:41;s:55:"Stops Draughts Under External Doors and Soaks Up Water.";i:42;s:198:"Measure the gap between the bottom of your door and the floor and then cut the strip to a suitable length making sure that the bristles of the brush reach the floor before screwing the bar in place.";i:43;s:72:"Rubber hinged flap draught excluders are installed in a similar fashion.";i:44;s:68:"A garage door stop weather stripping seal is either rubber or vinyl.";i:45;s:146:"Install it onto your wooden garage door stop moulding by attaching it to the door jamb until it almost touches the front face of your garage door.";i:46;s:27:"Garage Door Threshold Seal.";i:47;s:71:"A garage door threshold seal attaches to the floor instead of the door.";i:48;s:112:"For draught proofing doors and sash windows the best products to use are tack-on sprung metal or plastic strips.";i:49;s:70:"These can either feature a rubber strip or a compressible rubber seal.";i:50;s:73:"These are ideally suited to be positioned to the sides and tops of doors.";i:51;s:115:"Garage doors are equipped with a strip of rubber at the bottom to seal the garage doors opening while it is closed.";i:52;s:123:"It also protects the ground beneath the garage door and the garage door itself from being damaged when opening and closing.";i:53;s:53:"Rodents often like to chew through this rubber strip.";}}